1
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,291
[NARRATOR]
Beasts known as The Nemesis

2
00:00:11,375 --> 00:00:13,458
wreak havoc on mankind.

3
00:00:13,541 --> 00:00:16,083
The only humans
who can stand against them

4
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:18,000
are those called sorcerers.

5
00:00:18,083 --> 00:00:21,541
However, sorcerers are seen
as tainted by most,

6
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:25,958
and are regarded
with fear and distrust.

7
00:00:26,041 --> 00:00:30,458
[HAMELINE gasping]

8
00:00:30,541 --> 00:00:33,541
Go, Seth.

9
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:36,541
Don't let anyone stop you.

10
00:00:36,625 --> 00:00:38,375
Change the whole world.

11
00:00:38,458 --> 00:00:40,250
[blade withdraws]

12
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:42,375
♪

13
00:00:53,708 --> 00:00:55,458
[screaming]

14
00:00:55,541 --> 00:00:57,125
[MELIE]
Seth, wait!

15
00:00:57,208 --> 00:01:01,833
[screaming continues]

16
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:03,750
[SETH straining, grunts]

17
00:01:06,416 --> 00:01:08,375
He's hurt.

18
00:01:08,458 --> 00:01:11,750
Let that be a lesson to you,
ya damn insect!

19
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,791
[TORQUE]
Von Teppes.

20
00:01:13,875 --> 00:01:16,791
It ill-befits an Inquisitor
of your station

21
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:19,500
-to act so impul--
-I realize that, General.

22
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:21,791
But since you say
this one is dangerous,

23
00:01:21,875 --> 00:01:23,625
it seems important
that we be sure

24
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,291
the brat's down for the count.

25
00:01:25,375 --> 00:01:26,958
Please, no!

26
00:01:29,458 --> 00:01:31,083
[BOTH gasp]

27
00:01:32,083 --> 00:01:33,000
[TEPPES screams]

28
00:01:33,083 --> 00:01:34,541
[MELIE gasps]

29
00:01:34,625 --> 00:01:36,541
[TORQUE]
Is this it?

30
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:40,958
[wind rushing, whistling]

31
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:48,000
[SETH groans]

32
00:03:20,375 --> 00:03:23,958
[NARRATOR] "The Light That
Follows the Darkness"

33
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:27,000
[wind rushing, whistling]

34
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:39,916
[GRIMM] That's a tremendous
amount of Fantasia.

35
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,708
How'd he undergo
such a change?

36
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:43,541
I've got no idea.

37
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:44,958
I've seen Seth fight,

38
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:47,208
but I've never seen him
do anything like this.

39
00:03:47,291 --> 00:03:49,666
[SANTORI]
Oh!

40
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,666
[laughs]

41
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,916
Such awe-inspiring power.

42
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,291
A boy with horns
is one to be feared.

43
00:03:56,375 --> 00:03:57,500
Focus, Santori.

44
00:03:57,583 --> 00:03:59,000
We're supporting you
in this fight,

45
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,541
don't waste our strength.

46
00:04:00,625 --> 00:04:03,000
Forgive my distractible nature.

47
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:05,666
[TEPPES groaning]

48
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,916
That repugnant little brat!

49
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
How dare he leave
a mark on my face?!

50
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:11,833
What did I just
tell you, Von Teppes?

51
00:04:11,916 --> 00:04:15,291
Time to die!

52
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:16,375
[grunts]

53
00:04:16,458 --> 00:04:19,333
[booming thud]

54
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:22,041
I'll have words for that fool.

55
00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:25,416
[GRIMM] He defeated
a Thaumaturge with ease.

56
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,416
I...I'm not sure

57
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,958
-Seth's in there.
-[SETH growls]

58
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:32,375
[SANTORI grunts]

59
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:38,583
[SETH growls]

60
00:04:40,916 --> 00:04:42,541
[SANTORI grunts]

61
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:46,333
[SANTORI laughs]

62
00:04:46,416 --> 00:04:49,625
That boy is quite something
once his anger's aroused.

63
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:53,416
I shall require about two
minutes for rest and recovery.

64
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:56,208
[ULLMINA] Santori, look!
Rubble's falling on the town!

65
00:04:56,291 --> 00:04:57,250
[LISELOTTE and SANTORI]
Hmm?

66
00:04:57,333 --> 00:05:00,291
[CITIZENS screaming]

67
00:05:02,291 --> 00:05:04,750
[SANTORI]
Rest easy, citizens!

68
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:08,250
You are now under the protection
of the Thaumaturges!

69
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:11,541
[SETH growls]

70
00:05:11,625 --> 00:05:13,708
[TORQUE]
You're like a rampaging beast.

71
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:16,208
It seems I'll have
to put you down

72
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:18,750
before you destroy
what's left of this city.

73
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,958
[screaming]

74
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:29,291
Father of the Inquisition
and founder of all miracles.

75
00:05:29,375 --> 00:05:32,750
Let darkness give way
to the brilliance of your light.

76
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,333
[SETH growls]

77
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:51,500
-[TORQUE grunts]
-[SETH yells, groans]

78
00:05:51,583 --> 00:05:53,041
The wound I've given you

79
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:56,416
will soon nullify your ability
to ever wield Fantasia.

80
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,916
You won't hold that form
for much longer.

81
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,625
[SETH growls, grunts]

82
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:01,708
[TORQUE]
Hmm?

83
00:06:02,958 --> 00:06:05,208
[wind rushing]

84
00:06:05,291 --> 00:06:07,458
[SANTORI grunting]

85
00:06:07,541 --> 00:06:11,041
How has that boy lasted this
long against General Torque?

86
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:13,875
Once Santori's done
licking his wounds, we can help.

87
00:06:13,958 --> 00:06:17,000
[laughs]
It won't be long now.

88
00:06:17,083 --> 00:06:20,166
-[SETH straining]
-[TORQUE straining, grunts]

89
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:26,166
[SANTORI grunts]

90
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:28,750
[crumbling]

91
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:37,000
He escaped our grasp.

92
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:39,791
Did you see what became
of the other two sorcerers?

93
00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:42,083
[SANTORI]
Please forgive me, General.

94
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:44,708
I was focused on
protecting the people below,

95
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:46,458
and lost sight of them.

96
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:48,291
[TORQUE]
It's fine.

97
00:06:48,375 --> 00:06:51,666
Many people were saved today
because of your efforts.

98
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,125
For now, that's good enough.

99
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:56,083
Liselotte will handle
reconnaissance,

100
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,375
and Ullmina
will lead the rescue team.

101
00:06:58,458 --> 00:07:00,125
Relay these orders.

102
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:01,875
I'll go and find out
what happened

103
00:07:01,958 --> 00:07:03,500
to that fool Von Teppes.

104
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:05,250
[SANTORI]
Very well, General.

105
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:07,500
We shall do as you command.

106
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:19,916
[MELIE]
Seth...

107
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,333
what happened back there?

108
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:25,125
It was like something...

109
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:26,583
possessed you.

110
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:33,750
[GRIMM] There isn't time
to reflect on the past.

111
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:38,000
This area will soon be crawling
with Inquisition search parties.

112
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:41,000
In that case,
why did we land here?

113
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:44,291
[GRIMM] Because Grimm
has unfinished business.

114
00:07:48,541 --> 00:07:49,833
You're free.

115
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:51,625
Return to your homes.

116
00:07:51,708 --> 00:07:53,041
[MELIE nervously exhales]

117
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:55,875
--[ZOMBIES moaning]
-[MELIE yelping]

118
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:58,833
Grimm? You mind
explaining yourself?

119
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:00,083
[GRIMM]
These are people who either

120
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:02,291
came into contact
with the Nemeses,

121
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:04,125
or witnessed
Konrad's evil deeds.

122
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:05,291
What?

123
00:08:05,375 --> 00:08:07,333
[GRIMM]
Their lives were in danger,

124
00:08:07,416 --> 00:08:09,416
so Grimm put them
somewhere safe.

125
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:12,833
[MELIE] You mean, you were
behind all those abductions,

126
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:16,041
but you only did it
to protect the people?

127
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:18,166
[GRIMM]
Those "abductions?"

128
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:20,791
Hmm... Grimm understands now.

129
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:24,541
You're describing how Grimm's
actions were perceived, yes?

130
00:08:24,625 --> 00:08:27,833
Yeah. That's right.

131
00:08:27,916 --> 00:08:29,750
[MELIE] Making his intentions
clear to people

132
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:32,208
doesn't seem to be
Grimm's strong suit.

133
00:08:32,291 --> 00:08:34,291
-[DOC grunting, straining]
-[MELIE gasps]

134
00:08:34,375 --> 00:08:36,291
-[MELIE] Doc!
-[DOC shrieks]

135
00:08:36,375 --> 00:08:38,458
I don't wanna be shut up
inside stuff anymore.

136
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:39,708
I don't wanna!

137
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:40,958
First, it was that
smelly old dumpster,

138
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:42,250
and now, it's this weird,
dark coffin.

139
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:45,291
Get me outta here
Melie, I wanna go home!

140
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:47,750
Okay, first of all,
please quiet down.

141
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:50,250
If you keep screaming like that,
you're gonna get all of us

142
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,083
locked up in something
called a prison cell,

143
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:53,625
and we don't want
that now do we?

144
00:08:53,708 --> 00:08:55,583
How are we gonna get off
this island with Doc and Seth,

145
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:56,875
this is terrible--

146
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:59,083
[GRIMM] Seems that problem
solved itself.

147
00:08:59,166 --> 00:09:00,250
Look there.

148
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:01,708
[DOC and MELIE scream]

149
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,458
[train chugging, dinging]

150
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:05,208
[MELIE]
Hold on...

151
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:06,916
that thing's from Artemis!

152
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,000
You think it came for us?

153
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:10,833
[MC over loudspeaker]
What's up, y'all!

154
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:13,916
I come out here
at King Majesty's request!

155
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,791
Is The Debt King
down there with ya?

156
00:09:15,875 --> 00:09:18,708
-[train whistle blows]
-[DOC and MELIE gasp]

157
00:09:20,375 --> 00:09:21,958
[ULLMINA]
Everyone.

158
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,750
Do keep in mind that aiding
the wounded is our top priority!

159
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:27,833
Searching for the escaped
sorcerer can wait until later.

160
00:09:27,916 --> 00:09:29,541
It's awful...

161
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:32,458
to think that he managed
to escape General Torque.

162
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:34,916
Only the most despicably
cunning of sorcerers

163
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,375
could achieve such a feat.

164
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:38,541
We face a truly fearsome foe.

165
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:39,416
[BOTH SOLDIERS]
Right.

166
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:40,416
Uh...

167
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:45,625
-[TORQUE] Dragunov.
-[DRAGUNOV] Huh?

168
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:48,125
[DRAGUNOV]
General Torque.

169
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:51,125
I listened to your report
regarding Captain Konrad.

170
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,875
My deepest apologies.

171
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:56,250
I tried, but was still unable
to stop his rampage.

172
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:59,583
[TORQUE] That was due
to a failure of my own.

173
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:02,500
All accounts indicate that
you stayed calm under duress

174
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:05,083
and led the effort to save
these blameless people.

175
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,750
[DRAGUNOV]
Sir...

176
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:09,666
[TORQUE] Konrad was unable to
keep his emotions in check,

177
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,000
and so he was
brought to justice.

178
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:13,833
That's all there
is to be said.

179
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:16,291
[DRAGUNOV exhales]

180
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:18,500
[SANTORI snoring]

181
00:10:18,583 --> 00:10:20,750
-[fireworks explode]
-[SANTORI] Huh?

182
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,041
What?!

183
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:24,083
We're being attacked
yet again, it seems!

184
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:26,541
But why, and from where,
and by whom?

185
00:10:26,625 --> 00:10:28,625
Don't let the light
show distract you.

186
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:31,708
They're trying to use it
as cover so they can escape.

187
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:34,458
Whoa. 'Scuse me, but look!

188
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:37,708
[fireworks exploding, continues]

189
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:40,666
[LISELOTTE scoffs]
Decoy balloons?

190
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:43,000
Those sorcerers are ridiculous.

191
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:45,833
♪

192
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,875
[MALE CITIZEN]
Fireworks!

193
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:52,500
[FEMALE CITIZEN
So pretty.

194
00:10:52,583 --> 00:10:53,958
Feels like a festival.

195
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:55,458
[BABY laughs]

196
00:10:55,541 --> 00:10:58,041
Perhaps it's to finally signal
the conflict's end.

197
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,541
I'll take it as a sign

198
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:02,000
that things will get better
from this day forward.

199
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:03,666
Thanks, Seth.

200
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:07,041
You really made
a difference here.

201
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,000
[sniffles]

202
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:13,250
[fireworks exploding, continues]

203
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:20,708
[MELIE exhales]

204
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:24,125
[train chugging]

205
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:27,541
[train whistles]

206
00:11:37,583 --> 00:11:40,041
[MELIE shudders]

207
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:42,333
[MC over loudspeaker]
Thank you for flying with us.

208
00:11:42,416 --> 00:11:44,666
Our next stop
is the end of the line:

209
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:47,708
The Artemis Institute!

210
00:12:02,875 --> 00:12:05,208
[SETH groaning, pained]

211
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:07,666
[SETH]
Where... am I?

212
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:10,291
♪

213
00:12:12,375 --> 00:12:14,583
[inaudible]

214
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:21,125
-[inaudible]
-[SETH gasps]

215
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:24,416
[inaudible]

216
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,375
♪

217
00:12:26,458 --> 00:12:28,833
[inaudible]

218
00:12:28,916 --> 00:12:31,375
♪

219
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:36,083
[inaudible]

220
00:12:38,083 --> 00:12:40,083
Wait...

221
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:43,666
did I just watch...
my own memories?

222
00:12:46,583 --> 00:12:48,250
[gasps]

223
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:50,375
You're here with me,
Hameline?

224
00:12:52,708 --> 00:12:55,041
I'm sorry...

225
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:57,833
If not for me,
you wouldn't have...

226
00:12:59,916 --> 00:13:02,166
[HAMELINE exhales]

227
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:04,875
[HAMELINE] Goodbye Seth.
Take care.

228
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:09,208
[SETH crying softly]

229
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:15,666
There must've been
a way to save her.

230
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,708
I shouldn't have run.

231
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:26,083
I only went there
to capture a Nemesis.

232
00:13:26,166 --> 00:13:28,833
How did things end up
turning out this way?

233
00:13:28,916 --> 00:13:31,708
Ultimately,

234
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:34,583
all I did was add
to the chaos.

235
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:37,541
What did you do to me?

236
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:40,416
Hey Piodon!

237
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,791
I just asked you a question.

238
00:13:41,875 --> 00:13:43,916
Answer it!

239
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:47,541
I had no choice,

240
00:13:47,625 --> 00:13:50,041
because you were about
to get yourself killed.

241
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:53,333
There was only one way to save
your life and that was it.

242
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:56,083
No one asked you
to do that!

243
00:13:56,166 --> 00:13:57,750
What was your preference?

244
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,583
Are you really gonna tell me
that you would rather

245
00:13:59,666 --> 00:14:02,583
I let you and your friends
be killed by the Thaumaturges?

246
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:05,250
[SETH exhales]

247
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,250
I'm glad to be alive,

248
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:10,083
but I couldn't
tell friend from foe.

249
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:12,875
And also,
while I was berserk,

250
00:14:12,958 --> 00:14:14,791
I saw these strange images.

251
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:17,375
Like memories, but not mine.

252
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:18,958
So was it you, or not?

253
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:20,708
What did you do to me?

254
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:22,833
Not a lot.

255
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:25,708
That was your own power
you were just fighting with.

256
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:28,500
It's been dormant,
but it was always inside of you.

257
00:14:28,583 --> 00:14:31,250
You're saying that was me?

258
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:34,250
[PIODON] Everything you see
surrounding you now,

259
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:37,000
is a part of who you are.

260
00:14:37,083 --> 00:14:38,583
All of this is mine?

261
00:14:38,666 --> 00:14:40,500
Okay, but what is it?

262
00:14:40,583 --> 00:14:42,458
[PIODON]
Well...

263
00:14:42,541 --> 00:14:43,708
there are parts of yourself

264
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:45,750
that you still have
trouble accessing.

265
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:48,291
Powers and memories
that, for one reason

266
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:50,875
or another,
are locked away.

267
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:52,833
All I did was let a little
out of the cage for you.

268
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:54,375
[SETH exhales]

269
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:57,000
I don't understand this.

270
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:59,291
Why would you help me?

271
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:01,083
Who are you?

272
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:03,041
And why do you look like me?

273
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:07,916
We're not brothers. Are we?

274
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,833
Ya worked it out... huh...

275
00:15:10,916 --> 00:15:12,708
Yeah... of course we are.

276
00:15:12,791 --> 00:15:13,791
[SETH gasps]

277
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:15,583
It's the truth.

278
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:18,541
You're my kid brother, Seth.

279
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:20,291
[SETH gasps]

280
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:21,916
[SETH]
So...

281
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,875
we're really family?

282
00:15:23,958 --> 00:15:25,208
How do you know?

283
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:26,458
[PIODON]
I just do.

284
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:27,708
Don't believe me?

285
00:15:27,791 --> 00:15:29,541
[SETH]
I'm not sure...

286
00:15:29,625 --> 00:15:31,291
[PIODON]
That's all right.

287
00:15:31,375 --> 00:15:33,125
[SETH breathes shakily]

288
00:15:34,666 --> 00:15:37,291
[PIODON] You seem pretty
down in the dumps.

289
00:15:37,375 --> 00:15:41,166
[sighs] I thought that whenever
I met a bad guy,

290
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:42,708
I could just beat them
senseless,

291
00:15:42,791 --> 00:15:45,125
and everything would
work out all right.

292
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:47,458
But then...

293
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:51,875
I met Hameline and realized
how naïve that was.

294
00:15:53,958 --> 00:15:55,541
In the end...

295
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:57,500
I couldn't help her.

296
00:15:57,583 --> 00:15:59,416
Don't beat yourself up.

297
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,208
You still managed
to take down Konrad.

298
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:05,333
[SETH] Yeah, but I know there
are lots more people out there

299
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:07,125
who are just like him.

300
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:09,666
People who discriminate,
who hurt others

301
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:12,125
because they're
different from them.

302
00:16:12,208 --> 00:16:14,916
Maybe I'm a fool to think
I can change the world.

303
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,125
Even if I have
the power you say I do,

304
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:19,000
even if I find Radiant,

305
00:16:19,083 --> 00:16:20,541
will it be enough?

306
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:22,916
Is there even
any point in trying?

307
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:27,458
I can't tell you,

308
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:30,125
because I don't know
one way or the other.

309
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:33,333
[SETH] Please.
Just let me be alone right now.

310
00:16:33,416 --> 00:16:35,541
See you later.

311
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:45,416
[SETH exhales]

312
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:50,833
I'm... useless.

313
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:54,000
I couldn't save her.

314
00:16:54,083 --> 00:16:56,291
I couldn't save anyone.

315
00:16:56,375 --> 00:17:00,000
♪

316
00:17:14,083 --> 00:17:15,416
[MELIE]
Come on.

317
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:18,416
How long is the punk
gonna stay asleep for?

318
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,375
The sorcerer who was
treating his injuries

319
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:22,208
told me that we could
expect him to wake up

320
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,041
just about any minute now.

321
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:26,708
Do you mind tellin' me
what the heck happened to him?

322
00:17:26,791 --> 00:17:28,791
I'm planning to
ask that myself,

323
00:17:28,875 --> 00:17:31,250
if he'd wake up and get out
of my damn bed already.

324
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:33,041
It can't bother you
too much,

325
00:17:33,125 --> 00:17:34,291
or you would have
kicked him out

326
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:36,333
instead of lookin'
after him like this.

327
00:17:36,416 --> 00:17:38,083
You must be
pretty worried, huh?

328
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:39,416
-Huh?
-[DOC shrieks]

329
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,708
No violence, please!

330
00:17:40,791 --> 00:17:42,708
Ya gotta be gentle with me,
I'm a baby!

331
00:17:42,791 --> 00:17:44,416
[MELIE]
Shove it in your ear.

332
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,375
You're still an old man inside!

333
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:48,291
[DOC]
Have some sympathy, will ya?!

334
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:50,541
You think I wanted
to get sick, and molt,

335
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,625
and crawl outta myself
as an infant?

336
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:55,000
That really is
a disgusting curse.

337
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:58,291
Do you think I don't know that
without havin' you tell me?!

338
00:17:58,375 --> 00:18:01,541
Oh, man. How am I gonna
explain this body to Melba?

339
00:18:01,625 --> 00:18:03,583
Once she's seen me
as a weird baby,

340
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:05,625
any chance I might've had
with her will go kaput!

341
00:18:05,708 --> 00:18:06,916
Yeah...

342
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,875
there wasn't much chance
to start.

343
00:18:08,958 --> 00:18:11,000
Hey, take it back!

344
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:13,833
-[SETH groans]
-[DOC and MELIE gasp]

345
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:16,083
-[SETH groans]
-[DOC] Seth!

346
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:18,125
You feelin' okay, buddy?

347
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:20,000
Hey, Doc.

348
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:21,375
Melie.

349
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,916
You scared me.

350
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,375
Uh--

351
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:27,375
[huffs]

352
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:30,416
[gasps]
Seth, I...

353
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,958
[crying]
I'm so glad that you're okay.

354
00:18:33,041 --> 00:18:35,333
[MELIE continues crying]

355
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,166
Don't cry.

356
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,541
Wait a sec.

357
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:40,083
Where are we?

358
00:18:40,166 --> 00:18:42,500
We're in Melie's bedroom
back at Artemis.

359
00:18:42,583 --> 00:18:43,875
Believe it or not,

360
00:18:43,958 --> 00:18:46,416
you've been unconscious
for about a week now.

361
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,125
For a whole week?

362
00:18:48,208 --> 00:18:51,166
Yeah, you just wouldn't wake up
even after you were treated,

363
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:52,875
and no one
had any idea why.

364
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:54,250
It was horrible.

365
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,666
I was starting to think
you would never wake up.

366
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,500
I had no idea
how to help you.

367
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:00,833
Sorry, Melie, I'm okay.

368
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:03,791
[groans]
Huh?

369
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:05,791
[SETH]
These bandages...

370
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,500
did Grimm do this?

371
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:10,291
[DOC yells] Ahh! Why'd you
have to say his name?!

372
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:11,833
You're playin' with fire, kid!

373
00:19:11,916 --> 00:19:14,541
What if that bandaged
creep shows up again?

374
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,041
[GRIMM]
Grimm will assume

375
00:19:16,125 --> 00:19:18,250
that you're referring to
a different bandaged creep.

376
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:20,625
[DOC screams]
He really did show up!

377
00:19:20,708 --> 00:19:22,541
-[DOC swoons]
-[SETH] Grimm, hey!

378
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:24,833
[GRIMM]
You seem to have recovered.

379
00:19:24,916 --> 00:19:26,416
Grimm is happy to see that.

380
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,250
It looks like you
saved my butt again.

381
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,500
I owe you big.

382
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:30,708
[GRIMM]
No need for thanks.

383
00:19:30,791 --> 00:19:31,916
[SETH]
Mm--

384
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,458
[GRIMM]
If Grimm had not mistaken

385
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:36,541
your party for companions
of that Domitor,

386
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:39,750
Grimm could have lent you
his assistance sooner.

387
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,541
-Yeah, you got that right!
-[SETH] Hm?

388
00:19:41,625 --> 00:19:43,875
I had the wrong
idea about you at first, too.

389
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:45,375
Anyway, if it weren't for--

390
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:47,291
-[SETH groans in pain]
-[MELIE] Seth!

391
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:50,125
[GRIMM] Those wounds were
inflicted by General Torque.

392
00:19:50,208 --> 00:19:53,000
Among his miracles,

393
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:55,166
is the power
to nullify Fantasia.

394
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:58,125
His blade can slice
through magic with ease,

395
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:01,458
and render a sorcerer's
catalyst unusable.

396
00:20:01,541 --> 00:20:04,000
Wounds inflicted by
that power of his,

397
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:06,000
cannot be healed
by any magic.

398
00:20:06,083 --> 00:20:07,541
[SETH exhales]

399
00:20:07,625 --> 00:20:09,250
[GRIMM]
In the worst case,

400
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:12,791
you may never be able to wield
Fantasia with that arm again.

401
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:14,625
That sure would suck.

402
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:15,875
Although come to think of it,

403
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,875
that might actually be
for the best.

404
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:19,125
-[MELIE exhales]
-[DOC] Huh?

405
00:20:19,208 --> 00:20:21,166
What do I use these arms to do?

406
00:20:21,250 --> 00:20:23,333
They mostly just hurt people.

407
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:26,750
♪

408
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:28,291
[MELIE and DOC sigh]

409
00:20:28,375 --> 00:20:29,833
[GRIMM]
Hmm.

410
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:33,208
How could I forget to ask?

411
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:34,541
What happened to Rumble Town?

412
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:37,708
[GRIMM] The Thaumaturges
have restored order.

413
00:20:37,791 --> 00:20:40,291
And the rebuilding
process has begun.

414
00:20:40,375 --> 00:20:43,125
As for what the
town's future will look like...

415
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:44,375
there's no telling.

416
00:20:44,458 --> 00:20:45,875
But with Konrad gone,

417
00:20:45,958 --> 00:20:48,541
it should at least be better off
than it was before.

418
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:51,958
That's good to hear.

419
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:54,291
So despite all our efforts,

420
00:20:54,375 --> 00:20:57,333
turns out it was the Inquisition
who saved Rumble town.

421
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:58,708
Come on!

422
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:00,291
You helped, too.

423
00:21:00,375 --> 00:21:03,041
More importantly, I was stressed
out and exhausted

424
00:21:03,125 --> 00:21:04,666
and I got nothin' for it!

425
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:06,291
I was so determined
to run away

426
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:09,583
that I even forgot to collect
my money from the client!

427
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:11,208
And now I look like an infant!

428
00:21:11,291 --> 00:21:13,041
[crying] It could be
eighteen years before Melba

429
00:21:13,125 --> 00:21:14,750
sees me as a man again!
[sobbing]

430
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:17,625
Maybe you should to woo someone
who likes you back, like Devi!

431
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:19,750
Devi and I aren't even
the same species!

432
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,916
[MELIE] As long as you have
love, you can overcome anything!

433
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,958
-[DOC] No! Not a chance!
-[MELIE] Sure there is!

434
00:21:24,041 --> 00:21:25,333
Just go for it!

435
00:21:25,416 --> 00:21:26,916
[DOC] There's nothing to go for,
ya big weirdo!

436
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,541
-[SETH] Hey Melie.
-[DOC and MELIE gasp]

437
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:30,375
What about her
Nemesis brothers?

438
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:31,875
We brought them back with us.

439
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:34,000
The academy has
a whole enclosure

440
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:35,708
for captured Nemeses.

441
00:21:35,791 --> 00:21:37,333
They're living
there peacefully.

442
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:39,416
Thank goodness.

443
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:41,875
I'm glad we could protect them,
if nothing else.

444
00:21:41,958 --> 00:21:43,916
-[DOC sighs]
-[MELIE] Aw...

445
00:21:48,916 --> 00:21:51,375
[MAJESTY chewing]
Mmm! Yummy!

446
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:54,083
[chewing and humming]

447
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:55,833
[MC]
Between the Magic Locomotive,

448
00:21:55,916 --> 00:21:59,166
and the fireworks and balloons
we used as a diversion,

449
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:01,500
you ended up burning through
quite a bit of funding

450
00:22:01,583 --> 00:22:03,125
just to save one boy.

451
00:22:03,208 --> 00:22:06,916
[MAJESTY] Hmm... meow,
did I give any such order?

452
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,708
I suddenly forget.

453
00:22:08,791 --> 00:22:10,041
[MAJESTY]
You're pushing your luck,

454
00:22:10,125 --> 00:22:13,083
"inpurrupting" my snack time.
Shoo! Shoo!

455
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:16,666
[MC] Right then.
I'll leave ya to it, Majesty.

456
00:22:20,125 --> 00:22:21,541
[MAJESTY]
Hmm.

457
00:22:21,625 --> 00:22:23,375
Well, meow.

458
00:22:23,458 --> 00:22:26,416
I dare say, the claws
are about to come out.

459
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,000
Eh, boy?

460
00:22:28,083 --> 00:22:31,958
♪

461
00:24:08,125 --> 00:24:10,166
[NARRATOR] Now that they've
returned to Artemis,

462
00:24:10,250 --> 00:24:12,916
Seth, Melie, and Doc
are all three hailed

463
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,708
as champions for exposing
the evils of the Inquisition.

464
00:24:16,791 --> 00:24:18,666
Despite the merriment
around him,

465
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:20,583
Seth finds his heart
still tormented

466
00:24:20,666 --> 00:24:21,958
by grief and resentment.

467
00:24:22,041 --> 00:24:23,375
And that's when he finds

468
00:24:23,458 --> 00:24:25,708
Alma has come
to pay him a visit.

469
00:24:25,791 --> 00:24:27,333
Next time on Radiant,

470
00:24:27,416 --> 00:24:29,916
"The World That You Changed."

